channel.title: 8 YEAR'S but im back!
channel.description: Hello everyone, just dropping by to say HI!, most of you do not know me at all, 8 years ago i was all over the RSPS dev community's recently i took back to learning some new programming languages and when i got back into java, i thought rsps would be great refresher course, how ever looking back now lol i knew alot more java then i remembered :D. anyways like i said just saying Hi!

item.title: 8 YEAR'S but im back!
item.dc:creator: @Ruby_Forums_Coder Ruby
item.description:
@Ruby_Forums_Coder wrote:

[quote=“RUNE-PK, post:32, topic:550140”][quote author=Ruby link=topic=669051.msg4474455#msg4474455 date=1424900670]

Been good, long story short, got into drugs few years back, cleaned up 2.5 years ago been clean ever since got back into programming, just finished with C and C++ decided java was next and i always enjoyed RSPS so here i am

Java is my drug

This is probably the gayest thing you’ve ever said.

Is it gay that I was born in the wrong generation? I love coding, not drugs!

And then you have me that likes both.
[size=1pt]caffeine is a drug[/size]

Well i am very happy for you and your “AMAZING” life choices, how ever that being said, If you are only going to judge other peoples life choices, please keep it off of my post, i nor have the time, place or tolerance level to be dealing with someone who is ignorant enough to call another person “Gay” for loving programming.
That is his decision and the immaturity in your comment just leads me to believe you have never even been with a girl, so nuff talk bout all that java book titties grabbing, buddy, because logically speaking, women go towards men who will provide them with a comfortable life style, support, and success, not some drop out drug addict who thinks they like him cause he does drugs.

#Rekt GG lmao probably the funniest topic I’ve read all day xD welcome back tho

Not rekt at all. I have an incredibly well paid job, a load of friends, a great car, great living conditions. Just because someone enjoys drugs recreationally doesn’t make them a drop out drug addict. If I was stereotyping him like what he done I could say that I probably paid more in tax last year than he made, but thats none of my business.
[/quote]

Ruby, Obviously you didn’t understand what i was saying… Lol. But good job with your life i guess. But anyways have a good day. :D[/quote]

Ohhhh you quoted the wrong thing. My bad dude, thought you were siding with this asshat of a person.
